"step_by_step_thinking": "The provided documents discuss beta thalassemia, specifically its effects on erythrocytes. In the document '[Reaction between anti-erythrocyte-membrane immune sera and erythrocytes of patients with homozygous beta-thalassemia. Observations made with immunofluorescence and immunoperoxidase methods]', it is stated that 'Enhanced staining has been found in a number of mature and immature red blood cells...'. This suggests that the red blood cells in beta thalassemia are not macrocytic, as they can be in other conditions. The same document also mentions the presence of plasma proteins sticking to the surface of erythrocytes, which is consistent with microcytic and hypochromic erythrocytes. Finally, the document 'Frequencies of thalassemia in American blacks' states that individuals with beta thalassemia have decreased mean corpuscular hemoglobin (MCH) values. This further supports the conclusion that the red blood cells in beta thalassemia are microcytic and hypochromic.",
